<div align="center"><table width="50%" border="0"><tr><td valign="top"><b>Links</b></td></tr><tr><td><ul>

Unpublished synonymy:  Nomada capillata � male - Holotype seen at MCZ in April of 2006.  The type matches in all characteristics of size and coloration with that of N. illinoensis.  The only difference is that the scutellum instead of being red has two interior patches of yellowish dots that fade to orange around the edges.  I have not seen any other specimens that match and believe this type to be only a slightly different specimen of this species. 

Unpublished synonymy: Nomada minima - male - Holotype seen at the MCZ in April of 2006.  This species has all the characteristics of a small male illinoense.  I have a series of specimens that matches.  Antenna and coloration do not match parva.







<li><a href="#Hosts">Hosts</a></li>
</ul></td></tr></table></div>
